    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Lorenza</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Lorenza</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“It was a jest, but since you’re interested... House Aurelian has always feared the old science. They destroyed everything they could and sealed everything they couldn’t.

“Fortunately, they didn’t know Maadoran as well as my family did. Did you know that my House used to rule this city for centuries, long before Lord Gaelius’ forefather had it seized from us by force? The city’s ancient. Say the word and its secrets will be yours to discover.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts>
        <string>aod.quest_AG4_lorenzaKnowledge = true;</string>
      </onLoadScripts>
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Just like that?”</text>
          <def_link>3275</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“I’m sorry.”</text>
          <def_link>3276</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>3274</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Lorenza</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Lorenza</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“Just like that. I don’t fear dusty old tablets and trinkets. Whatever power they may have held once is long gone, but even if it’s not... Putting a trinket around your neck won’t make you a Magus, no more than strapping a sword would make you a warrior.

“In my experience, a blade in the darkness is far more dangerous than dusty old scrolls. Speaking of which,” Lorenza looks you dead in the eyes, “have you made your decision yet?”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“You have a deal, lady. What do you want me to do?”</text>
          <def_link>3279</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“No dice. For what it's worth, I’m sorry.”</text>
          <def_link>3276</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>3275</UID>
